snippet: In East Jerusalem, late-night move-ins by Jewish settlers are raising tensions and questions about ownership of the properties.
abstract: Jerusalem Journal; late-night move-ins by Jewish settlers in East Jerusalem are raising tensions and questions about ownership of the properties; episode has created a more intimate web of intrigue and recrimination, as Palestinian residents harbor suspicions and trade rumors about who among their relatives or neighbors may have cooperated with Arab brokers who transferred the properties into the settlers’ hands.
lead_paragraph: In East Jerusalem, late-night move-ins by Jewish settlers are raising tensions and questions about ownership of the properties.

headline.main: A House-by-House Struggle for Control of a Jerusalem Neighborhood
headline.print_headline: A House-by-House Struggle for Control of a Neighborhood
